# [MLS](../wg/mls.html)

## Summary
The MLS Working Group met at IETF 125 to discuss the status of active drafts and several new proposals. Key highlights include the progression of post-quantum (PQ) cipher suites and the PQ combiner toward publication, the separation of targeted messages into a standalone document, and discussions on optimizing MLS for two-party scenarios and reducing signature overhead. The group also addressed privacy enhancements for external commits and the integration of web token credentials.

## Key Discussion Points

### Working Group Status and Active Drafts
*   **Partial MLS (formerly Light MLS):** **Richard Barnes** reported that the draft is stable and implemented in MLS-PP. **Nick Sullivan** noted low review counts; a poll showed approximately 5-10 participants had read it. **Richard Barnes** will update the draft to prepare for a future Working Group Last Call (WGLC).
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-extensions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-extensions/):** **Raphael Robert** presented on [Extensions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-extensions-00). The draft is down to one open issue regarding gatekeeping in federated contexts. **Rohan Mahy** proposed an "opaque dictionary" extension to allow members to handle unknown components without cryptographic eviction. The draft will undergo editorial polishing before a second WGLC.
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-targeted-messages](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-targeted-messages/):** **Raphael Robert** presented [Targeted Messages](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-targeted-messages-00). This is now a standalone draft.
    *   Discussion focused on whether to add ratcheting. **Richard Barnes** and **Raphael Robert** expressed caution against re-inventing the Double Ratchet, preferring to keep the mechanism "one-shot."
    *   **Rohan Mahy** suggested a wrapper to allow a single message to be sent to multiple specific recipients (e.g., moderators).
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-pq-ciphersuites](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-pq-ciphersuites/):** **Rohan Mahy** presented [ML-KEM and Hybrid Cipher Suites for MLS](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-ml-kem-and-hybrid-cipher-suites-for-mls-00). The draft now includes nine cipher suites to balance performance and security (AES-128/256 and SHA-256/384). There was strong support for moving this to WGLC.
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-combiner](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-combiner/):** **Marta Garijo** presented [A PQ MLS](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-a-pq-mls-00). The draft was renamed "Amortized PQ MLS Combiner." It now aligns with the Safe API from the extensions draft. It is considered ready for a final WGLC following a pending PR.
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-virtual-clients](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-virtual-clients/):** **Konrad Kohbrok** presented [Virtual Clients](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-virtual-clients-00). The draft is merging with the Subgroup proposal. Implementation experience in OpenMLS revealed complexities in processing self-commits and managing randomness.

### Additional Drafts and Proposals
*   **Fewer Signatures:** **Konrad Kohbrok** presented [Fewer Signatures](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-fewer-signatures-00). The goal is to reduce signature overhead by hashing the outer message into the leaf node signature. **Rohan Mahy** cautioned about potential "circular dependency" issues in internal commits where the group context must be hashed.
*   **MLS Two Party Profile:** **Konrad Kohbrok** presented [MLS Two Party Profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-mls-two-party-profile-01). This profile aims to use MLS for 1:1 connections (like TLS/QUIC handshakes) to provide Post-Compromise Security (PCS).
    *   **Richard Barnes** noted Cisco IPR and suggested waiting for broader IETF consensus (SECDISPATCH/SAG) on where this work should live.
    *   **Ye (Huawei)** queried the comparison to the Signal Protocol; **Konrad Kohbrok** noted that MLS is a specialization from group logic down to 1:1, ensuring consistent security proofs.
*   **[draft-ietf-mls-ratchet-tree-options](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mls-ratchet-tree-options/):** **Rohan Mahy** presented [Ratchet Tree Options](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-ratchet-tree-options-01). The draft was formally adopted. Security considerations were added, and unnecessary tree signatures were removed.
*   **Private External Commits and External Proposals:** **Rohan Mahy** presented [Private External Commits and External Proposals](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-private-external-commits-and-external-proposals-00). The proposal uses HPKE to encrypt external commits/proposals so the Distribution Service (DS) cannot see group metadata. It is currently implemented in OpenMLS and used by Farcaster/XMTP.
*   **Web Token Credentials:** **Rohan Mahy** presented [Web Token Credentials (and others)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-mls-web-token-credentials-and-others-00), proposing SD-JWT and SD-CWT as credential types for MLS to support selective disclosure.
*   **Protocol Gaps:** **Rohan Mahy** concluded with a list of remaining MLS gaps, including malicious member replays, group forking via malicious update paths, and signature validation for blinded DS environments.

## Decisions and Action Items
*   **Decision:** `draft-ietf-mls-ratchet-tree-options` is formally adopted as a Working Group item.
*   **Decision:** `draft-ietf-mls-pq-ciphersuites` will proceed to Working Group Last Call.
*   **Decision:** `draft-ietf-mls-combiner` will proceed to Working Group Last Call after **Marta Garijo** submits the final PR.
*   **Action Item:** **Richard Barnes** to update the Partial MLS draft (bump version) to facilitate WGLC.
*   **Action Item:** **Rohan Mahy** to submit a PR for the "opaque dictionary" in `draft-ietf-mls-extensions`.
*   **Action Item:** **Konrad Kohbrok** to review the "Klein bottle" circularity concern regarding `draft-kohbrok-mls-fewer-signatures`.

